        "Titelbild": "Asylum-Seekers.png (https://v5.airtableusercontent.com/v1/17/17/1685498400000/qB2XSnPV2D94aC7EEAbHSQ/u8wtuRyHai5yKQXtEb_cysbxAqV5EgEsI9f9PtYclyHv_e_4nBX2IrlXmerMSQ1-iUy2gWP21GQm1TD14HYPCsEkLS9wYiVwqPyOQR5vYlw/6Rulfo71_oecxlDelI8q4uE8AEaM0Pieq0OZY4B4CWU)",
        "TextBeschreibung": "The project „Asylum Seekers“ shows the immigration of refugees into Europe in the yeas 2013. It is a prototype for an interactive application to inform about the european refugee situation. It compares each country by the ratio between acceptances and rejections regarding asylums. Each circle is representing a country and is separated in two rings consisting of points. Every point is representing 50 refugees seeking for an asylum. While the outer ring displays the refugees rejected by the country the inner ring depicts the refugees who got an asylum or are allowed to stay for a period of time. In addition a legend on the left side shows those numbers in comparison. The size of the countries depends on the number of inhabitants. So if the points are very condensed, there are many asylum seekers measured against inhabitants. The lines emitting from each european country are displaying the commonest origins of the immigrants. The information is based on data published on the websites of Eurostat, the european commission for statistics and the UN Refugee Agency.",
